  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hong Kong LGBT+ training for 200 Service Providers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Hong Kong, LGBT people exists in all kinds of occupations. However, sexual orientation discrimination and gender identity issues may be a problem for some LGBT people when they need medical and counselling services. Providing training to service providers allows them to understand the needs of the LGBT+ community. In our project, there will be 4 sharing sessions &amp; 5 education trainings for 200 service providers. There will also be 10 volunteer trainings and 2 exhibitions for public education.</narrative>
  </description>
